{"title_page": "Madan Dulloo", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|honorific-prefix  = [[The Honourable]]\n| name          = Madan Dulloo<br/> \u092e\u0926\u0928 \u0921\u0932\u0942\u0913 <br/> <small>\n|honorific-suffix  =\n| image         = Madan Dulloo.jpg\n| caption       = \n| order         = [[Former]] [[Member of parliament]]\n| president    = \n| primeminister= \n| term_start   = \n| term_end     = \n| predecessor  = \n| successor = \n| order3        = \n| president3    = \n| primeminister3= \n| term_start3   = \n| term_end3     = \n| order4         = \n| president4     = \n| primeminister4 = \n| term_start4    = \n| term_end4      = \n| predecessor4   = \n| successor4    = \n| order1         = \n| president2    = \n| primeminister2 = \n| term_start2    = \n| term_end2     = \n| predecessor2   = \n| successor2   = \n| president1    = \n| primeminister1 = \n| term_start1    = \n| term_end1      = \n| predecessor1   = \n| successor1    = \n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1949|09|20}}\n| birth_place   = \n| spouse        =\n| children      =\n| party         = \n| alma_mater    = [[University of London]]\n| occupation    = [[Politician]], [[Barrister]] and [[Diplomat]]\n| religion      = \n| website     = \n}}\n\n'''Madan Murlidhar Dulloo''', born 20 September 1949, is a barrister, politician and diplomat from [[Mauritius]].\n\nA law graduate from the [[University of London]], member of the [[Middle Temple]], Madan Dulloo was first elected during the 1976 general elections under the banner of the [[Mauritian Militant Movement]].\n\nMadan Dulloo is one of the longest serving Member of Parliament (29 years).  Madan Dulloo has been present in constituency No.6 (Grand Baie/Poudre D\u2019Or) since 1976 (34 years); Elected Member of Parliament for constituency No.6 (Grand Baie/Poudre D\u2019Or) at the following General Elections: 1976, 1982, 1983, 1987, 1991, 2000, 2005.\n\nMadan Dulloo is amongst those very few politicians in Mauritius who most of the times have always been elected (7 times).\n   \nMadan Dulloo is amongst those very few who stood the most times for General Elections (including by-elections) in Mauritius.\n\nIn 2005, Madan Dulloo was at his tenth (10th) elections. He has always been a candidate for the General Elections in constituency No.6 Grand-Baie/Poudre D\u2019or since 1976. It\u2019s a glorious track record.\n\nMadan Dulloo has held the following ministerial portfolios throughout his political career:\n* Minister of Foreign Affairs and Emigration\n* Minister of Agriculture, Fisheries, and Natural Resources\n* Attorney General and Minister of Justice\n* Minister of Foreign Affairs, International Trade and Cooperation\n\nBetween 1986 and 1994, Madan Dulloo was Minister of Foreign Affairs and Emigration, Minister of Agriculture, Fisheries & Natural Resources and Attorney General & Minister of Justice.\n\nBetween 2005 and 2008, Madan Dulloo was Minister of Foreign Affairs, International Trade and Cooperation.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* https://web.archive.org/web/20110130060532/http://www.madandulloo.com/\n* https://www.facebook.com/madan.dulloo\n* https://www.youtube.com/mrmadandulloo\n\n==External links==\n* {{Facebook|madan.dulloo}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dulloo, Madan}}\n[[Category:1949 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Foreign Ministers of Mauritius]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of London]]\n[[Category:University of Paris alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the National Assembly (Mauritius)]]\n[[Category:Mauritian Hindus]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of Mauritius]]\n[[Category:Mouvement Socialiste Militant politicians]]\n[[Category:Mauritian Militant Movement politicians]]\n[[Category:Mauritian lawyers]]\n[[Category:Mauritian politicians of Indian descent]]\n\n\n{{Mauritius-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|honorific-prefix  = [[The Honourable]]\n| name          = '''Madan Dulloo''' <br/> \u092e\u0926\u0928 \u0921\u0932\u0942\u0913 <br/> <small>\n|honorific-suffix  =\n| image         = Madan Dulloo.jpg\n| caption       = \n| order         = [[Former]] [[Member of parliament]]\n| president    = \n| primeminister= \n| term_start   = \n| term_end     = \n| predecessor  = \n| successor = \n| order3        = \n| president3    = \n| primeminister3= \n| term_start3   = \n| term_end3     = \n| order4         = \n| president4     = \n| primeminister4 = \n| term_start4    = \n| term_end4      = \n| predecessor4   = \n| successor4    = \n| order1         = \n| president2    = \n| primeminister2 = \n| term_start2    = \n| term_end2     = \n| predecessor2   = \n| successor2   = \n| president1    = \n| primeminister1 = \n| term_start1    = \n| term_end1      = \n| predecessor1   = \n| successor1    = \n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1949|09|20}}\n| birth_place   = \n| spouse        =\n| children      =\n| party         = \n| alma_mater    = [[University of London]]\n| occupation    = [[Politician]], [[Barrister]] and [[Diplomat]]\n| religion      = \n| website     = \n}}\n\n'''Madan Murlidhar Dulloo''', born 20 September 1949, is a barrister, politician and diplomat from [[Mauritius]].\n\nA law graduate from the [[University of London]], member of the [[Middle Temple]], Madan Dulloo was first elected during the 1976 general elections under the banner of the [[Mauritian Militant Movement]].\n\nMadan Dulloo is one of the longest serving Member of Parliament (29 years).  Madan Dulloo has been present in constituency No.6 (Grand Baie/Poudre D\u2019Or) since 1976 (34 years); Elected Member of Parliament for constituency No.6 (Grand Baie/Poudre D\u2019Or) at the following General Elections: 1976, 1982, 1983, 1987, 1991, 2000, 2005.\n\nMadan Dulloo is amongst those very few politicians in Mauritius who most of the times have always been elected (7 times).\n   \nMadan Dulloo is amongst those very few who stood the most times for General Elections (including by-elections) in Mauritius.\n\nIn 2005, Madan Dulloo was at his tenth (10th) elections. He has always been a candidate for the General Elections in constituency No.6 Grand-Baie/Poudre D\u2019or since 1976. It\u2019s a glorious track record.\n\nMadan Dulloo has held the following ministerial portfolios throughout his political career:\n* Minister of Foreign Affairs and Emigration\n* Minister of Agriculture, Fisheries, and Natural Resources\n* Attorney General and Minister of Justice\n* Minister of Foreign Affairs, International Trade and Cooperation\n\nBetween 1986 and 1994, Madan Dulloo was Minister of Foreign Affairs and Emigration, Minister of Agriculture, Fisheries & Natural Resources and Attorney General & Minister of Justice.\n\nBetween 2005 and 2008, Madan Dulloo was Minister of Foreign Affairs, International Trade and Cooperation.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* https://web.archive.org/web/20110130060532/http://www.madandulloo.com/\n* https://www.facebook.com/madan.dulloo\n* https://www.youtube.com/mrmadandulloo\n\n==External links==\n* {{Facebook|madan.dulloo}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dulloo, Madan}}\n[[Category:1949 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Foreign Ministers of Mauritius]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of London]]\n[[Category:University of Paris alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the National Assembly (Mauritius)]]\n[[Category:Mauritian Hindus]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of Mauritius]]\n[[Category:Mouvement Socialiste Militant politicians]]\n[[Category:Mauritian Militant Movement politicians]]\n[[Category:Mauritian lawyers]]\n[[Category:Mauritian politicians of Indian descent]]\n\n\n{{Mauritius-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Sinaloa", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madan_Dulloo"}
{"title_page": "Rim of the World", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 American science fiction film}}\n{{italic title}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Rim of the World\n| image          = File:Rim of the World (2019) poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Promotional release poster\n| director       = [[McG]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n*McG\n*Mary Viola\n*Susan Solomon-Shapiro\n*Matt Smith\n}}\n| writer         = [[Zack Stentz]]\n| screenplay     = \n| story          = \n| based on       = <!-- {{Based on|title of the original work|creator of the original work|additional creator(s), if necessary}} -->\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Jack Gore (actor)|Jack Gore]]\n*Miya Cech\n*[[Benjamin Flores Jr.]]\n*Alessio Scalzotto\n*[[King Bach|Andrew Bachelor]]\n*[[Annabeth Gish]]\n}}\n| narrator       = \n| music          = [[Bear McCreary]]\n| cinematography = [[Shane Hurlbut]]\n| editing        = [[Vincent Tabaillon]] \n| production companies       = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Wonderland Sound and Vision]]\n*Circle Of Confusion\n}}\n| distributor    = Netflix\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|5|24}}\n| runtime        = 99 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         =$19.0 million<ref>{{cite report|title=Film and Television Tax Credit Program Program 2.0|url=http://film.ca.gov/wp-content/uploads/CFC-Approved-Projects-List.pdf|publisher=[[California Film Commission]]|page=9|accessdate=October 4, 2018}}</ref>\n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Rim of the World''''' is a 2019 American [[Science fiction film|science fiction]] [[adventure film]] directed by [[McG]] from a screenplay by [[Zack Stentz]]. It stars [[Jack Gore (actor)|Jack Gore]], Miya Cech, [[Benjamin Flores Jr.]] and Alessio Scalzotto. The film, which was Stentz' modern take on the kid-centered action films of the 1980s,<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2019/05/into-the-woods-four-misfits-must-stave-off-an-alien-attack-in-rim-of-the-world/|title=New Netflix original Rim of the World is pretty much perfect summer fare|last=Ouellette|first=Jennifer|date=2019-05-26|website=Ars Technica|language=en-us|access-date=2019-06-04}}</ref> was streamed on [[Netflix]] on May 24, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://media.netflix.com/en/only-on-netflix/80218306|title=Rim of the World|website=Netflix Media Center|accessdate=2019-04-11}}</ref><ref name=\"Filmoria\">{{cite web |url=https://www.filmoria.co.uk/rim-of-the-world-will-launch-globally-on-netflix-on-24th-may-2019/|title=RIM OF THE WORLD launched globally on Netflix on 24th May 2019|publisher=Filmoria.co.uk|date= |accessdate=7 May 2019}}</ref> It was the most watched content in the SVOD service in the UK the week it was released, overtaking the series ''[[Dead to Me (TV series)|Dead to Me]]'' and ''[[Riverdale (2017 TV series)|Riverdale]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/rim-of-the-world-netflix-1202623519/|title=McG\u2019s Sci-Fi Feature \u2018Rim of the World\u2019 Crashes Into Netflix UK Top Spot With \u2018Dead To Me\u2019 Holding Steady In Second|last=White|first=Peter|last2=White|first2=Peter|date=2019-05-29|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-06-04}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n{{Long plot|film|date=January 2020}} Alex reluctantly attends a summer camp in southern California called \"Rim of the World\". He befriends two other \"misfits\" - ZhenZhen, a runaway from China, and Dariush, a teen from a rich but bankrupt family. While the campers are canoeing Dariush wanders off with Alex and find another young teen, Gabriel, a juvenile delinquent. While heading back to camp they witness incoming alien ships invading the valley, and also discover the camp has evacuated - all except for Conrad, a camp counselor. Suddenly, an escape pod from the International Space Station crashes into the place with a dying astronaut inside, who gives Alex a key that needs to get to NASA station JPL, deemed the only way to destroy the aliens. An alien appears with its \"dog\" and kills the astronaut, but Alex and his friends manage to fend it off and escape the camp.\n\nThey make their way to the Sheriff's Office and discover and inmate, Lou, who has been left behind. Alex decides to release him before the group continues on their way to JPL. The group is found by some Marines who take the key and put the children on a bus to take them to safety. However, aliens attack and kill the soldiers, so the group takes the key back and continues on their way to JPL. After stopping to rest for the night, they are attacked by a gang of masked individuals led by Lou. He agrees to let the teens go if Alex gives him the key. Alex refuses and right before Lou attacks him, the alien from the camp attacks them and Lou is killed, but the teens manage to escape.\n\nThe teens finally make it to JPL after being attacked by the alien for the third time, only to find that the doctor who needs the key is dead. The teens are able to make radio contact with a general who explains that the key can be used to destroy the alien mothership in orbit via a [[Cold War]] defense project named Excalibur. Zhenzhen goes into the basement to start the generators while Alex goes on the roof to the communication tower. Dariush and Gabriel stay in the command center of JPL to insert the key into the systems. Alex is attacked on the roof by the alien while Zhenzhen is attacked in the basement by an alien dog but manages to lock it in the basement and get back to the command room to help Gabriel, who cannot read the numbers, insert the launch key since Dariush passed out from blood loss due to an injury.\n\nAfter successfully inserting the launch keys, the General warns Zhenzhen, Dariush, and Gabriel to get out of the building because JPL is not safe and there are two units on the way to get them. In the meantime, Alex has managed to lure the alien into a highly flammable engine test room and burns the alien. With the building burning to the ground, Alex relives the traumatic events leading to his father's death. However, he moves past them and is able to escape just in time. The group of teens watch from the ground as the alien mothership is blown up in the atmosphere. Alex is reunited with his mother and the children are deemed as heroes. Pictures show the teens being knighted by Queen Elizabeth II, being awarded crowns and sashes, and riding in parades throughout America.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Jack Gore (actor)|Jack Gore]] as Alex\n* Miya Cech as ZhenZhen\n*[[Benjamin Flores Jr.]] as Dariush\n*Alessio Scalzotto as Gabriel\n*[[King Bach|Andrew Bachelor]] as Logan\n*[[Annabeth Gish]] as Grace\n*[[Scott MacArthur]] as Lou\n*Dean Jagger as Captain Hawking\n*[[Michael Beach]] as General Khoury\n*[[Lynn Collins]] as Major Collins\n*David Theune as Head Counselor\n*[[Tony Cavalero]] as Conrad\n*Carl McDowell as Carl\n*Punam Patel as Angeline\n*[[Jason Rogel]] as Customs Official\n*[[Chris Wylde]] as Uncle Chris\n*[[Rudy Mancuso]] as Wes\n*Amanda Cerny as Lucy\n*[[Allan Graf]] as Taxi Driver\n*Cameron Fuller as Young Soldier\n*Richard Gore as Alex's dad\n*[[Peter Parros]] as Dariush's dad\n*Annie Cavalero as Zip Line Counselor\n\n==Production==\nIn March 2018, it was reported that [[McG]] would direct ''Rim of the World'' for [[Netflix]] from a screenplay by [[Zack Stentz]]. In an interview, Stentz revealed that he started working on the script as early as 2017 and the deal with Netflix was closed a year later.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/story/rim-of-the-world-sci-fi-netflix/|title=Netflix's 'Rim of the World' Shows Where Sci-Fi Is Headed|last=Rogers|first=Adam|date=2019-05-24|work=Wired|access-date=2019-06-04|issn=1059-1028}}</ref> Principal production commenced in May 2018 in [[Los Angeles, California]].<ref>{{cite web |author=Mike Fleming Jr |url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/mcg-rim-of-the-world-netflix-1202348325/ |title=McG Sets 'Rim Of The World' At Netflix |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=March 20, 2018 |access-date=}}</ref><ref name=\"flickeringmyth.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.flickeringmyth.com/2018/03/mcg-to-direct-sci-fi-adventure-rim-of-the-world-for-netflix/|title=McG to direct sci-fi adventure Rim of the World for Netflix|author=|date=March 25, 2018|website=flickeringmyth.com|access-date=March 25, 2018}}</ref> In June 2018, the cast was announced.<ref name=\"cast\">{{cite web |author=Amanda N'Duka |url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/director-mcg-netflix-film-rim-of-the-world-cast-1202414461/ |title=McG Assembles Cast For Netflix Film 'Rim of the World' |date=June 20, 2018 |access-date=}}</ref>\n\n[[Principal photography]] began in June 2018<ref>{{cite web |author=Peter File|url=https://www.flickeringmyth.com/2018/06/mcg-fills-out-the-cast-of-netflix-feature-rim-of-the-world/|title=McG fills out the cast of his Netflix feature Rim of the World|date=June 24, 2018 |access-date=}}</ref><ref name=\"cast\"/> and reportedly lasted 40 days.\n\n==Reception==\nOn the [[review aggregator]] website, [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 25% based on 12 reviews, with a [[Weighted arithmetic mean|weighted average]] of 3.8/10.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/rim_of_the_world|title=Rim of the World (2019)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango Media]]|accessdate=May 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|8179388}}\n* {{Netflix title|80218306}}\n\n{{McG}}\n[[Category:2010s science fiction films]]\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Alien invasions in films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films about summer camps]]\n[[Category:Films directed by McG]]\n[[Category:Films set in California]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Netflix original films]]\n\n{{2010s-sf-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 American science fiction film}}\n{{italic title}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Rim of the World\n| image          = File:Rim of the World (2019) poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Promotional release poster\n| director       = [[McG]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n*McG\n*Mary Viola\n*Susan Solomon-Shapiro\n*Matt Smith\n}}\n| writer         = [[Zack Stentz]]\n| screenplay     = \n| story          = \n| based on       = <!-- {{Based on|title of the original work|creator of the original work|additional creator(s), if necessary}} -->\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Jack Gore (actor)|Jack Gore]]\n*Miya Cech\n*[[Benjamin Flores Jr.]]\n*Alessio Scalzotto\n*[[King Bach|Andrew Bachelor]]\n*[[Annabeth Gish]]\n}}\n| narrator       = \n| music          = [[Bear McCreary]]\n| cinematography = [[Shane Hurlbut]]\n| editing        = [[Vincent Tabaillon]] \n| production companies       = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Wonderland Sound and Vision]]\n*Circle Of Confusion\n}}\n| distributor    = Netflix\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|5|24}}\n| runtime        = 99 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         =$19.0 million<ref>{{cite report|title=Film and Television Tax Credit Program Program 2.0|url=http://film.ca.gov/wp-content/uploads/CFC-Approved-Projects-List.pdf|publisher=[[California Film Commission]]|page=9|accessdate=October 4, 2018}}</ref>\n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Rim of the World''''' is a 2019 American [[Science fiction film|science fiction]] [[adventure film]] directed by [[McG]] from a screenplay by [[Zack Stentz]]. It stars [[Jack Gore (actor)|Jack Gore]], Miya Cech, [[Benjamin Flores Jr.]] and Alessio Scalzotto. The film, which was Stentz' modern take on the kid-centered action films of the 1980s,<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2019/05/into-the-woods-four-misfits-must-stave-off-an-alien-attack-in-rim-of-the-world/|title=New Netflix original Rim of the World is pretty much perfect summer fare|last=Ouellette|first=Jennifer|date=2019-05-26|website=Ars Technica|language=en-us|access-date=2019-06-04}}</ref> was streamed on [[Netflix]] on May 24, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://media.netflix.com/en/only-on-netflix/80218306|title=Rim of the World|website=Netflix Media Center|accessdate=2019-04-11}}</ref><ref name=\"Filmoria\">{{cite web |url=https://www.filmoria.co.uk/rim-of-the-world-will-launch-globally-on-netflix-on-24th-may-2019/|title=RIM OF THE WORLD launched globally on Netflix on 24th May 2019|publisher=Filmoria.co.uk|date= |accessdate=7 May 2019}}</ref> It was the most watched content in the SVOD service in the UK the week it was released, overtaking the series ''[[Dead to Me (TV series)|Dead to Me]]'' and ''[[Riverdale (2017 TV series)|Riverdale]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/rim-of-the-world-netflix-1202623519/|title=McG\u2019s Sci-Fi Feature \u2018Rim of the World\u2019 Crashes Into Netflix UK Top Spot With \u2018Dead To Me\u2019 Holding Steady In Second|last=White|first=Peter|last2=White|first2=Peter|date=2019-05-29|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-06-04}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n{{Long plot|film|date=January 2020}} Alex reluctantly attends a summer camp in southern California called \"Rim of the World\". He befriends two other \"misfits\" - ZhenZhen, a runaway from China, and Dariush, a teen from a rich but bankrupt family. While the campers are canoeing Dariush wanders off with Alex and find another young teen, Gabriel, a juvenile delinquent. While heading back to camp they witness incoming alien ships invading the valley, and also discover the camp has evacuated - all except for Conrad, a camp counselor. Suddenly, an escape pod from the International Space Station crashes into the place with a dying astronaut inside, who gives Alex a key that needs to get to NASA station JPL, deemed the only way to destroy the aliens. An alien appears with its \"dog\" and kills the astronaut, but Alex and his friends manage to fend it off and escape the camp.\n\nThey make their way to the Sheriff's Office and discover and inmate, Lou, who has been left behind. Alex decides to release him before the group continues on their way to JPL. The group is found by some Marines who take the key and put the children on a bus to take them to safety. However, aliens attack and kill the the soldiers, so the group takes the key back and continues on their way to JPL. After stopping to rest for the night, they are attacked by a gang of masked individuals led by Lou. He agrees to let the teens go if Alex gives him the key. Alex refuses and right before Lou attacks him, the alien from the camp attacks them and Lou is killed, but the teens manage to escape.\n\nThe teens finally make it to JPL after being attacked by the alien for the third time, only to find that the doctor who needs the key is dead. The teens are able to make radio contact with a general who explains that the key can be used to destroy the alien mothership in orbit via a [[Cold War]] defense project named Excalibur. Zhenzhen goes into the basement to start the generators while Alex goes on the roof to the communication tower. Dariush and Gabriel stay in the command center of JPL to insert the key into the systems. Alex is attacked on the roof by the alien while Zhenzhen is attacked in the basement by an alien dog but manages to lock it in the basement and get back to the command room to help Gabriel, who cannot read the numbers, insert the launch key since Dariush passed out from blood loss due to an injury.\n\nAfter successfully inserting the launch keys, the General warns Zhenzhen, Dariush, and Gabriel to get out of the building because JPL is not safe and there are two units on the way to get them. In the meantime, Alex has managed to lure the alien into a highly flammable engine test room and burns the alien. With the building burning to the ground, Alex relives the traumatic events leading to his father's death. However, he moves past them and is able to escape just in time. The group of teens watch from the ground as the alien mothership is blown up in the atmosphere. Alex is reunited with his mother and the children are deemed as heroes. Pictures show the teens being knighted by Queen Elizabeth II, being awarded crowns and sashes, and riding in parades throughout America.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Jack Gore (actor)|Jack Gore]] as Alex\n* Miya Cech as ZhenZhen\n*[[Benjamin Flores Jr.]] as Dariush\n*Alessio Scalzotto as Gabriel\n*[[King Bach|Andrew Bachelor]] as Logan\n*[[Annabeth Gish]] as Grace\n*[[Scott MacArthur]] as Lou\n*Dean Jagger as Captain Hawking\n*[[Michael Beach]] as General Khoury\n*[[Lynn Collins]] as Major Collins\n*David Theune as Head Counselor\n*[[Tony Cavalero]] as Conrad\n*Carl McDowell as Carl\n*Punam Patel as Angeline\n*[[Jason Rogel]] as Customs Official\n*[[Chris Wylde]] as Uncle Chris\n*[[Rudy Mancuso]] as Wes\n*Amanda Cerny as Lucy\n*[[Allan Graf]] as Taxi Driver\n*Cameron Fuller as Young Soldier\n*Richard Gore as Alex's dad\n*[[Peter Parros]] as Dariush's dad\n*Annie Cavalero as Zip Line Counselor\n\n==Production==\nIn March 2018, it was reported that [[McG]] would direct ''Rim of the World'' for [[Netflix]] from a screenplay by [[Zack Stentz]]. In an interview, Stentz revealed that he started working on the script as early as 2017 and the deal with Netflix was closed a year later.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/story/rim-of-the-world-sci-fi-netflix/|title=Netflix's 'Rim of the World' Shows Where Sci-Fi Is Headed|last=Rogers|first=Adam|date=2019-05-24|work=Wired|access-date=2019-06-04|issn=1059-1028}}</ref> Principal production commenced in May 2018 in [[Los Angeles, California]].<ref>{{cite web |author=Mike Fleming Jr |url=https://deadline.com/2018/03/mcg-rim-of-the-world-netflix-1202348325/ |title=McG Sets 'Rim Of The World' At Netflix |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=March 20, 2018 |access-date=}}</ref><ref name=\"flickeringmyth.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.flickeringmyth.com/2018/03/mcg-to-direct-sci-fi-adventure-rim-of-the-world-for-netflix/|title=McG to direct sci-fi adventure Rim of the World for Netflix|author=|date=March 25, 2018|website=flickeringmyth.com|access-date=March 25, 2018}}</ref> In June 2018, the cast was announced.<ref name=\"cast\">{{cite web |author=Amanda N'Duka |url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/director-mcg-netflix-film-rim-of-the-world-cast-1202414461/ |title=McG Assembles Cast For Netflix Film 'Rim of the World' |date=June 20, 2018 |access-date=}}</ref>\n\n[[Principal photography]] began in June 2018<ref>{{cite web |author=Peter File|url=https://www.flickeringmyth.com/2018/06/mcg-fills-out-the-cast-of-netflix-feature-rim-of-the-world/|title=McG fills out the cast of his Netflix feature Rim of the World|date=June 24, 2018 |access-date=}}</ref><ref name=\"cast\"/> and reportedly lasted 40 days.\n\n==Reception==\nOn the [[review aggregator]] website, [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 25% based on 12 reviews, with a [[Weighted arithmetic mean|weighted average]] of 3.8/10.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/rim_of_the_world|title=Rim of the World (2019)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango Media]]|accessdate=May 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|8179388}}\n* {{Netflix title|80218306}}\n\n{{McG}}\n[[Category:2010s science fiction films]]\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Alien invasions in films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films about summer camps]]\n[[Category:Films directed by McG]]\n[[Category:Films set in California]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Netflix original films]]\n\n{{2010s-sf-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "Duplicate word removed", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rim_of_the_World"}
{"title_page": "2020 Indianapolis Colts season", "text_new": "{{short description|68th season in franchise history}}\n{{Infobox NFL season\n| team            = Indianapolis Colts\n| logo            = Indianapolis Colts new wordmark.svg\n| year            = 2020\n| record          = \n| division_place  = \n| coach           = [[Frank Reich]]\n| owner           = [[Jim Irsay]]\n| general manager = [[Chris Ballard (American football)|Chris Ballard]]\n| stadium         = [[Lucas Oil Stadium]]\n| playoffs        =\n| pro bowlers     =\n| uniform         = \n| shortnavlink    = Colts seasons\n}}\nThe [[2020 NFL season|2020 season]] will be the [[Indianapolis Colts]]' upcoming 68th in the [[National Football League]] and their 37th in [[Indianapolis]]. It will also be their third season under [[List of Indianapolis Colts head coaches|head coach]] [[Frank Reich]] and fourth under the leadership of general manager [[Chris Ballard (American football)|Chris Ballard]]. [[Philip Rivers]] signed a 1 year deal with $25 million in a new contract on March 17, 2020. Rivers is now the starting quarterback for this season.\n\nThe Colts will attempt to improve upon their [[2019 Indianapolis Colts season|7\u20139 season]] from the previous year and return to the playoffs. They will also attempt to win their first [[AFC South]] title since [[2014 NFL season|2014]].\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Draft==\n{{main|2020 NFL Draft}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Indianapolis Colts|year=2020|border=2}}\"| 2020 Indianapolis Colts Draft\n|-\n! Round !! Selection !! Player !! Position !! College\n|-\n\n|-\n! rowspan=2| 2 || 34\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE-->\n|-\n! 44\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE-->\n|-\n! 3 || 75\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE-->\n|-\n! 4 || 122\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE-->\n|-\n! 5 || 160\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE-->\n|-\n! 