anapolis Colts|year=2020|border=2}};text-align:center;\n|state=autocollapse\n|title=Week #: Indianapolis Colts at Detroit Lions&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n|date=\n|time=\n|road=Colts\n|R1=0|R2=0|R3=0|R4=0\n|home=Lions\n|H1=0|H2=0|H3=0|H4=0\n|stadium=[[Ford Field]], [[Detroit, Michigan]]\n|attendance=\n|weather=None (indoor stadium)\n|referee=\n|TV=\n|TVAnnouncers=\n|reference=\n|scoring=\n|stats=\n}}\n\n===Standings===\n====Division====\n{{2020 AFC South standings|team=IND}}\n====Conference====\n{{2020 AFC standings|team=IND}}\n-->\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.colts.com}}\n\n{{Indianapolis Colts}}\n{{Indianapolis Colts seasons}}\n{{2020 NFL season by team}}\n\n[[Category:2020 National Football League season by team|Indianapolis]]\n[[Category:Indianapolis Colts seasons]]\n[[Category:2020 in sports in Indiana|Indianapolis Colts]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|68th season in franchise history}}\n{{Infobox NFL season\n| team            = Indianapolis Colts\n| logo            = Indianapolis Colts new wordmark.svg\n| year            = 2020\n| record          = \n| division_place  = \n| coach           = [[Frank Reich]]\n| owner           = [[Jim Irsay]]\n| general manager = [[Chris Ballard (American football)|Chris Ballard]]\n| stadium         = [[Lucas Oil Stadium]]\n| playoffs        =\n| pro bowlers     =\n| uniform         = \n| shortnavlink    = Colts seasons\n}}\nThe [[2020 NFL season|2020 season]] will be the [[Indianapolis Colts]]' upcoming 68th in the [[National Football League]] and their 37th in [[Indianapolis]]. It will also be their third season under [[List of Indianapolis Colts head coaches|head coach]] [[Frank Reich]] and fourth under the leadership of general manager [[Chris Ballard (American football)|Chris Ballard]]. [[Philip Rivers]] signed a 1 year deal with $25 million in a new contract on March 17, 2020. Rivers is now the starting quarterback for this season.\n\nThe Colts will attempt to improve upon their [[2019 Indianapolis Colts season|7-9 season]] from the previous year and return to the playoffs. They will also attempt to win their first [[AFC South]] title since [[2014 NFL season|2014]].\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Draft==\n{{main|2020 NFL Draft}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Indianapolis Colts|year=2020|border=2}}\"| 2020 Indianapolis Colts Draft\n|-\n! Round !! Selection !! Player !! Position !! College\n|-\n\n|-\n! rowspan=2| 2 || 34\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE-->\n|-\n! 44\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE-->\n|-\n! 3 || 75\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE-->\n|-\n! 4 || 122\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE-->\n|-\n! 5 || 160\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE-->\n|-\n! rowspan=2| 6 || 193\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE-->\n|-\n! 197\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE-->\n|}\n\n==Staff==\n{{Indianapolis Colts staff}}\n\n==Current roster==\n{{Indianapolis Colts roster}}\n\n==Preseason==\nThe Colts' preseason opponents and schedule will be announced in the spring.\n\n==Regular season==\n<!--===Schedule===-->\n===2020 opponents===\nListed below are the Colts' opponents for [[2020 NFL season|2020]]. Exact dates and times will be announced in the spring.<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 Opponents Determined |url=https://nflcommunications.com/Pages/2020-Opponents-Determined.aspx |work=NFL Communications |date=December 30, 2019 |accessdate=December 30, 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Indianapolis Colts|year=2020|border=2}}\"| Category !! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Indianapolis Colts|year=2020|border=2}}\" width=200px| Home !! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Indianapolis Colts|year=2020|border=2}}\" width=200px| Away\n|-\n| '''Division opponents'''<br>([[AFC South]]) || colspan=2| [[2020 Houston Texans season|Houston Texan